A DAVEYTON councillor has been involved in an accident in which a person was knocked dead.Captain Kay Makhubela of the SAPS said the incident happened at midnight on Saturday.The councillor &ndash; who cannot be named &ndash; is now fighting for his life in hospital.Reliable sources told Daily Sun that the councillor was allegedly driving under the influence of alcohol at the time of the accident.Makhubela said he could not confirm the allegations being raised, but he added that all the circumstances surrounding the accident would be investigated.&ldquo;We cannot mention names. All we can say is, he is one of the councillors in Daveyton.&rdquo; The accident happened in Putfontein, near Daveyton. A culpable homicide case was opened.